benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails/{email} - Delete email from account

covered: Valid Request: Successful deletion scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC12, TC13, TC17, TC18, TC19) are well covered.
Non-Existent Resources: Tests for non-existent account (TC03) and non-existent email (TC04) are included.
Invalid Inputs: Tests for invalid accountId format (TC05), invalid email format (TC06), missing headers (TC07), and unsupported parameters (TC08).
Error Handling: Unauthorized access (TC10), system errors (TC11), and service unavailability are addressed.
Edge Cases: Very large email address (TC12), minimal-length email (TC13), and concurrent requests (TC15).
Regression Tests: Handling of uppercase emails (TC17), backward compatibility (TC18).
Timeout and Performance: Response time under threshold (TC14).
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with multiple emails and pagination.
Authorization: No explicit tests for role-based access control or token permissions beyond missing header.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests to verify throttling or rate limits.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test for caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Soft Deletes: No tests verify if deletion is soft (e.g., marked as deleted) or hard.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination when accounts have many emails to verify correct handling of large datasets.
Include authorization tests with different user roles and tokens to ensure proper access control.
Implement rate limiting tests to verify system stability under high request volumes.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behavior.
Test for soft delete behavior if applicable, to confirm whether emails are permanently removed or marked as deleted.
